Judge Young is the most aggressive, but he’s hardly the only judge ordering releases.
Across the country, immigrants in detention are rushing to federal courts to demand that judges release them, and by and large they’re winning their cases.
A federal court in San Francisco late last week ordered release of several migrants with diabetes or asthma.
Still other cases involve illegal immigrants nabbed at the border who were being held in order to serve as witnesses in cases against their smugglers.
